{"key":"processedPost-8528604","value":{"id":8528604,"first":8528263,"last":8528604,"when":1213596668,"utime":"06/16/08 09:11 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I am also going to cultivate shiitakes, I heard substituting sawdust for vermiculite in the substrate works, is this true? <br /></blockquote><br /><br />Yes.&nbsp; Shiitake will grow on regular brf cakes, or you can substitute sawdust for the verm and they'll do a little better.<br /><br />I agree with the above that if you have mycelium after less than three days, it is more than likely mold mycelium. The mushroom spores normally need 24 to 36 hours to germinate, and then need another 36 to 48 hours to grow enough to be visible to the naked eye.&nbsp; Buzzkill indeed. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/frown.gif\" alt=\":frown:\" title=\":frown:\"/><br />RR","title":"Re: Excited, plus a question"}}